  "slok27": {
    "_id": "BG13.27",
    "abhinav": {
      "author": "Sri Abhinav Gupta",
      "et":
          "13.27 Yavat etc.  Whatever is a thing, whether moving or unmoving - all this is born not as something altogether different from the Field and the Field-sensitizer.\t\n Therefore -",
      "sc":
          "।।13.27।।यावदिति।  यत्किंचित् चरम् अचरं च तत् सर्वं क्षेत्रज्ञातिरेकि न संभवतीति।"
    },
    "adi": {
      "author": "Swami Adidevananda",
      "et":
          "13.27 Whatever being is born, whether it is moving or stationary, know, O Arjuna, that it is through the combination of the Ksetra (body) and Ksetrajna (knower of the Field)."
